column34: Please let us know where you heard about us?

column10: A cyclist was riding north on West Taylor Parkway. A motorist also heading north was speeding. This motorist encountered the cyclist as well as another motorist heading south on West Taylor Parkway at the curve in the road near the intersection of Taylor and Dartmouth nearly hitting the cyclist. The cyclist had to make an avoidance maneuver in order to keep from being hit.
